HEADWORD: Hematotherma
<hw>Hem`a*to*ther"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <grk>a"i^ma</grk>, <grk>a"i`matos</grk>, blood +
<grk>thermo`s</grk> warm.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
warm-blooded vertebrates, comprising the mammals and birds; -- the
antithesis to <contr>hematocrya</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hematothermal</ent>⟦br⟧
